<br>
When this legislative effort started, I was roasted for potentially destroying the lawsuit and hobby plus having no chance of getting legislation introduced.  I was roasted a few times more every time I told you to write or call your Senator.  Let's look at the track record.  The bill was introduced to the Senate with several cosponsors.  Thanks to your phone calls and letters.  The bill was referred to the Senate Judiciary Committee where we did not have many friendly faces.  Again, your phone calls and letters put a smile on many of those faces and added three cosponsors from that committee.  This did not happen through the leadership and wisdom of John Kyte, the only guy making money out of all of this.  No, it happened because you responded when you were asked to.  For that, you people deserve the credit.  I'm just the loose cannon that got you started.<br>
<br>
We are in fairly good shape in the Senate, but no so in the House.  This is no surprise and was anticipated.  With our limited resources we had to focus on one body at a time.  We are now in a position to divert some of those resources to the House.  In fact, it is now absolutely necessary.  We need a bill that can leave the Senate and have friendly faces in the House Judiciary.  At the moment, we don't have those friendly faces on the House Judiciary Committee.  Outreach efforts by Senate staff have not produced any results here and it time for the House members to hear from the people who voted them into office.  What a novel concept!<br>
<br>
We know the ATFE is not going to change the proposed 62.5 gram rule.  The argument that we need to write letters to the ATFE or they will tell Congress nobody cares is ridiculous.  I wish the ATFE would do that as Senate staff will tell them how some Senate offices were shut down for a day by your phone calls.  Remember that?  That was another loose cannon episode as I seem to recall.  No, the reason we are asking you to write to the ATFE<br>
and send a copy to your Representative with a cover letter is that it is a marvelous opportunity to get a discussion going on this issue with your Representative.  For a change, they will hear the truth on this issue from the people who voted them into the office.  It will be an eye opener for most of them and a breath of fresh air from the lies the ATFE has been telling them.<br>
<br>
So the choice is up to you.  You can listen to the backseat drivers or you can listen to the person who got you this far.<br>
<br>
You may repost this if you wish.<br>
<br>
John Wickman<br>
ARSA<br>
<br>
