Letter &amp; Phone Campaign For Senate Judiciary Committee<br>
from <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.space-rockets.com/congress">www.space-rockets.com/congress</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
June 15, 2003 - The purpose of a new letter campaign is to persuade Senators on the committee that unrestricted access to rocket propellant as defined in S724 is not going cause Homeland security problems. The campaign will also focus on getting Senators to vote independently and not follow one Senators lead. Most importantly, we do not want S724 to emerge out of committee this week with weight limitations. We do not have to get out of committee with a unanimous vote, just a simple majority.<br>
<br>
see <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.space-rockets.com/letter.html">www.space-rockets.com/letter.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> for information on the letter and phone campaign.<br>
