S724 Blocked By A Few Senators And Democratic Party Block Voting<br>
from <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.space-rockets.com/arsanews#bill3">www.space-rockets.com/arsanews#bill3</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
June 15, 2003 - Senate bill S724 is being held in committee by Senators Kohl and Hatch until weight limits are imposed on it. Senator Kohl, one of the authors of the Safe Explosive Act (SEA), has been against S724 from the beginning. Since Kohl is an author of the SEA, all other Democrats on the committee, except Senator Durbin, have decided to follow Senator Kohl's lead on the matter. Senator Hatch is uncomfortable with permitting American citizens to have unrestricted access to ammonium perchlorate composite rocket propellant. The weight limits being discussed within the committee are extremely low. As a result ARSA has started a new letter and phone campaign in the hopes of turning this situation around.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
ATFE On Senator Kohl's Staff<br>
from <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.space-rockets.com/arsanews#kohlatf">www.space-rockets.com/arsanews#kohlatf</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
June 15, 2003 - Senator Herb Kohl representing the state of Wisconsin has had ATFE agents on his staff since 2001. Senator Kohl is one of the coauthors of the Safe Explosives Act (SEA) which was strongly endorsed by the ATFE and was added as an amendment to the Homeland Security Act. The SEA has resulted in widespread disruptions in the transportation of explosives in the United States. <br>
<br>
Senator Kohl's SEA has also created a major crisis for hobby rocketry and &quot;hands on&quot; aerospace education programs within the United States. Senator Mike Enzi from Wyoming has introduced Senate bill S724 to fix these problems. The bill has 12 cosponsors. Currently, the bill is trapped in the Senate Judiciary Committee where Senator Kohl is a member. Other Democrats on the committee, except Senator Durbin, are deferring to Senator Kohl on the bill. The ATFE is strongly opposed to S724 as is Senator <br>
<br>
<br>
